    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Context passing is how downstream agents in a handoff chain learn what upstream agents already did. Without it, every agent starts blind and re-derives information. With it, each agent receives accumulated knowledge \u2014 findings, decisions, metadata \u2014 and builds on top. In LangGraph, context lives in a shared ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "TypedDict",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " state. The two primary carriers are a ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "context: dict[str, Any]",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " field for structured data and a ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "messages: list[BaseMessage]",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " field for conversation history."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "image",
        "attrs": {
          "src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,",
          "alt": "Context passing: agents accumulate findings, analysis, and reports in a shared context dict across handoffs",
          "title": "Context Passing Pattern"
        }
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Designing the Context-Carrying State"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "import operator\nfrom typing import Annotated, Any\nfrom typing_extensions import TypedDict\nfrom langchain_core.messages import BaseMessage\n\n\nclass ContextState(TypedDict):\n    # Structured carry-forward context \u2014 each agent merges into this\n    context: dict[str, Any]\n    # Full conversation history \u2014 appended by every agent\n    messages: Annotated[list[BaseMessage], operator.add]\n    # Top-level goal set at invocation time\n    goal: str\n    # Terminal output\n    final_output: str"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "context",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " dict is last-write-wins, so each agent must merge its additions with the existing value: ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{**state[\"context\"], \"new_key\": value}",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ". The ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "messages",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " list uses ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "operator.add",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " so parallel agents can each append without overwriting each other."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Building Up Context Across Agents"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\nfrom langchain_core.messages import AIMessage\n\nllm = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\n\n\ndef researcher(state: ContextState) -> dict:\n    response = llm.invoke(f\"Research: {state['goal']}\")\n    return {\n        \"messages\": [AIMessage(content=response.content, name=\"researcher\")],\n        # Additive merge: spread existing context, add new key\n        \"context\": {\n            **state[\"context\"],\n            \"research_findings\": response.content,\n            \"research_done\": True,\n        },\n    }\n\n\ndef analyst(state: ContextState) -> dict:\n    # Read upstream context written by researcher\n    findings = state[\"context\"].get(\"research_findings\", \"No research available\")\n    prompt = f\"Analyse these findings:\\n{findings}\"\n    response = llm.invoke(prompt)\n    return {\n        \"messages\": [AIMessage(content=response.content, name=\"analyst\")],\n        \"context\": {\n            **state[\"context\"],\n            \"analysis\": response.content,\n            \"key_insights\": _extract_insights(response.content),\n        },\n    }\n\n\ndef writer(state: ContextState) -> dict:\n    # Access everything accumulated so far\n    ctx = state[\"context\"]\n    findings = ctx.get(\"research_findings\", \"\")\n    analysis = ctx.get(\"analysis\", \"\")\n    insights = ctx.get(\"key_insights\", [])\n\n    prompt = (\n        f\"Write a report based on:\\n\"\n        f\"Research: {findings}\\n\"\n        f\"Analysis: {analysis}\\n\"\n        f\"Key insights: {insights}\"\n    )\n    response = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-sonnet-5\").invoke(prompt)\n    return {\n        \"messages\": [AIMessage(content=response.content, name=\"writer\")],\n        \"context\": {**ctx, \"report_written\": True},\n        \"final_output\": response.content,\n    }\n\n\ndef _extract_insights(text: str) -> list[str]:\n    \"\"\"Parse bullet points as insight strings.\"\"\"\n    lines = [l.strip().lstrip(\"\u2022-*\").strip() for l in text.split(\"\\n\")]\n    return [l for l in lines if len(l) > 20][:5]"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Namespacing Context Keys"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "When many agents write to the same context dict, key collisions silently overwrite data. Namespace keys by agent name or stage to avoid this:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "# Instead of:\nreturn {\"context\": {**state[\"context\"], \"output\": result}}\n\n# Use namespaced keys:\nreturn {\"context\": {**state[\"context\"], \"researcher__output\": result}}\n\n# Or nest by agent:\nreturn {\n    \"context\": {\n        **state[\"context\"],\n        \"researcher\": {\n            \"output\": result,\n            \"confidence\": 0.9,\n            \"sources\": [\"source1\", \"source2\"],\n        },\n    }\n}\n\n# Downstream agents read with get + default:\ndef analyst(state: ContextState) -> dict:\n    researcher_ctx = state[\"context\"].get(\"researcher\", {})\n    findings = researcher_ctx.get(\"output\", \"No research available\")\n    confidence = researcher_ctx.get(\"confidence\", 0.0)\n    ..."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Nested dicts are safer for complex pipelines. Flat namespaced keys (",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "\"researcher__output\"",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": ") work well when you want easy JSON serialisation without nested structures."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Using Message History as Context"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "For LLM agents that benefit from seeing the full conversation, pass the message history directly into the LLM call. Each agent appends its own output, so every downstream agent automatically sees everything that came before:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langchain_core.messages import SystemMessage, HumanMessage, AIMessage\n\n\ndef researcher_with_history(state: ContextState) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Pass full message history to the LLM \u2014 it sees all prior agent outputs.\"\"\"\n    system = SystemMessage(content=\"You are a researcher. Build on prior conversation.\")\n    # state[\"messages\"] already contains HumanMessage + any prior AIMessages\n    response = llm.invoke([system] + state[\"messages\"])\n    return {\n        \"messages\": [AIMessage(content=response.content, name=\"researcher\")],\n        \"context\": {**state[\"context\"], \"research\": response.content},\n    }\n\n\ndef analyst_with_history(state: ContextState) -> dict:\n    system = SystemMessage(\n        content=\"You are an analyst. The conversation above contains prior research.\"\n    )\n    # Messages now include the researcher's AIMessage\n    response = llm.invoke([system] + state[\"messages\"])\n    return {\n        \"messages\": [AIMessage(content=response.content, name=\"analyst\")],\n        \"context\": {**state[\"context\"], \"analysis\": response.content},\n    }"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "This approach works best for chains of 3\u20135 agents where the full history fits in the model's context window. For longer chains, trim the history to the most recent N messages or summarise earlier turns before passing them on."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Trimming Context for Long Chains"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from langchain_core.messages import trim_messages\nfrom langchain_anthropic import ChatAnthropic\n\n_summariser = ChatAnthropic(model=\"claude-haiku-4-5-20251001\")\n\n\ndef summarise_context(state: ContextState, max_tokens: int = 4000) -> dict:\n    \"\"\"Compress message history when it grows too large.\"\"\"\n    if len(state[\"messages\"]) <= 6:\n        return {}  # nothing to trim yet\n\n    # Keep last 4 messages verbatim; summarise everything before\n    recent = state[\"messages\"][-4:]\n    older = state[\"messages\"][:-4]\n\n    summary_prompt = [\n        HumanMessage(\n            content=f\"Summarise this conversation in 3 bullet points:\\n\"\n                    + \"\\n\".join(m.content for m in older if hasattr(m, \"content\"))\n        )\n    ]\n    summary = _summariser.invoke(summary_prompt)\n    summary_msg = AIMessage(\n        content=f\"[Summary of prior conversation]\\n{summary.content}\",\n        name=\"summariser\",\n    )\n    return {\"messages\": [summary_msg] + recent}  # replaces full history\n\n\ndef trim_context_dict(ctx: dict[str, Any], keep_keys: list[str]) -> dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Keep only the specified keys in the context dict.\"\"\"\n    return {k: v for k, v in ctx.items() if k in keep_keys}"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Summarisation preserves semantic content without growing the token count proportionally. Insert a ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "summarise_context",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " node between pipeline stages rather than inside every agent node."
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "horizontalRule"
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Type-Safe Context with Dataclasses"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Raw dicts are flexible but lose type safety. Replace the context dict with a typed dataclass when the schema is known upfront:"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "codeBlock",
        "attrs": {
          "language": "python"
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "from dataclasses import dataclass, field\n\n\n@dataclass\nclass PipelineContext:\n    research_findings: str = \"\"\n    analysis: str = \"\"\n    key_insights: list[str] = field(default_factory=list)\n    report_written: bool = False\n    metadata: dict[str, Any] = field(default_factory=dict)\n\n\nclass TypedContextState(TypedDict):\n    goal: str\n    ctx: PipelineContext      # replaces dict[str, Any]\n    messages: Annotated[list[BaseMessage], operator.add]\n    final_output: str\n\n\ndef researcher_typed(state: TypedContextState) -> dict:\n    response = llm.invoke(state[\"goal\"])\n    # Replace ctx with an updated copy \u2014 dataclass is immutable-style\n    old_ctx = state[\"ctx\"]\n    new_ctx = PipelineContext(\n        research_findings=response.content,\n        analysis=old_ctx.analysis,\n        key_insights=old_ctx.key_insights,\n        report_written=old_ctx.report_written,\n        metadata=old_ctx.metadata,\n    )\n    return {\n        \"messages\": [AIMessage(content=response.content, name=\"researcher\")],\n        \"ctx\": new_ctx,\n    }"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "The dataclass approach eliminates string-key typos and makes it obvious what each agent produces and consumes. The tradeoff is verbosity when updating \u2014 consider using ",
            "marks": []
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "dataclasses.replace(old_ctx, research_findings=response.content)",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "code"
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": " to create updated copies cleanly."
          }
        ]
      },
